1
00:00:39,075 --> 00:00:40,545
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,545 --> 00:00:41,975
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:00:44,945 --> 00:00:49,555
Momo promised she'd raise my baby well.

4
00:00:50,755 --> 00:00:52,855
We were as close as sisters.

5
00:00:55,865 --> 00:00:56,865
It's Mommy.

6
00:00:57,625 --> 00:01:00,835
Thank you for taking
such good care of the baby.

7
00:01:02,235 --> 00:01:03,235
Thank you so much.

8
00:01:03,805 --> 00:01:06,235
You poor thing.
You kept saying you felt dizzy.

9
00:01:07,105 --> 00:01:08,705
How could this happen?

10
00:01:12,245 --> 00:01:13,245
The poor thing.

11
00:01:14,445 --> 00:01:16,485
At least he got to see
his mother's face...

12
00:01:17,845 --> 00:01:19,385
Don't worry.

13
00:01:24,325 --> 00:01:26,325
(Ju Shin)

14
00:01:27,955 --> 00:01:30,125
- Hello?
- Ba Ra...

15
00:01:30,525 --> 00:01:31,765
passed away at dawn.

16
00:01:34,265 --> 00:01:35,835
There won't be a funeral
before the burial.

17
00:01:53,755 --> 00:01:56,325
Is her granddaughter
really moving in next week?

18
00:01:56,525 --> 00:01:58,585
Yes. I spoke with her on the phone.

19
00:02:03,725 --> 00:02:05,395
I think I'm going to miss him.

20
00:02:06,065 --> 00:02:07,765
You should come and visit sometime.

21
00:02:07,835 --> 00:02:09,405
I'll text you the address.

22
00:02:10,165 --> 00:02:12,105
- Would that be okay?
- Of course.

23
00:02:14,335 --> 00:02:16,805
Thank you. I know she was grateful too.

24
00:02:16,805 --> 00:02:17,905
It was nothing.

25
00:02:17,975 --> 00:02:19,945
Ba Ra asked me to.

26
00:02:20,115 --> 00:02:22,615
- I've been paid more than enough.
- Please, I insist.

27
00:02:25,655 --> 00:02:26,655
Goodness.

28
00:02:26,985 --> 00:02:29,255
You should go back in.
The grandmother is all by herself.

29
00:02:29,725 --> 00:02:30,725
Right.

30
00:02:42,035 --> 00:02:46,105
She's not just a pretty face,
but an angel.

31
00:03:07,755 --> 00:03:08,755
Ba Ra.

32
00:03:11,195 --> 00:03:12,535
How could you leave me...

33
00:03:15,735 --> 00:03:16,865
and just go like that?

34
00:03:19,705 --> 00:03:21,275
How could you?

35
00:03:46,265 --> 00:03:48,195
That looked like Geum Ba Ra, the reporter.

36
00:03:49,605 --> 00:03:51,705
Well, I can just check.

37
00:03:54,505 --> 00:03:55,975
(Reporter Geum Ba Ra)

38
00:03:58,045 --> 00:04:00,815
The number you have dialed
is not in service.

39
00:04:01,145 --> 00:04:03,585
Please check the number and dial again.

40
00:04:06,055 --> 00:04:08,785
The number you have dialed
is not in service.

41
00:04:09,125 --> 00:04:12,395
- Please check the number and dial again.
- I'm heading out.

42
00:04:12,995 --> 00:04:13,995
Okay.

43
00:04:18,325 --> 00:04:20,595
Was she in a car accident or something?

44
00:04:38,145 --> 00:04:41,555
Shouldn't the baby see his mother off?

45
00:04:42,985 --> 00:04:46,725
Be sure to burp him
and lay him down gently on his side.

46
00:04:48,225 --> 00:04:50,595
He sometimes spits up, even after burping.

47
00:04:51,065 --> 00:04:52,065
Got it.

48
00:05:19,395 --> 00:05:20,795
(Momo)

49
00:05:24,965 --> 00:05:26,765
(Momo)

50
00:05:30,635 --> 00:05:33,375
- Yes...
- The press will be there,

51
00:05:33,835 --> 00:05:35,675
so I think we should go together.

52
00:05:37,905 --> 00:05:39,175
I'm downstairs.

53
00:05:58,565 --> 00:05:59,595
Seatbelt.

54
00:07:39,465 --> 00:07:40,995
She was in the prime of her life.

55
00:08:32,145 --> 00:08:33,155
What's wrong?

56
00:10:58,595 --> 00:11:02,295
Book us a table at the Ria Hotel buffet.
For just us two.

57
00:11:02,365 --> 00:11:05,065
No. You know what will happen
if you overeat.

58
00:11:05,135 --> 00:11:07,405
Don't worry.
I will just eat in moderation.

59
00:11:07,675 --> 00:11:09,745
You think you can restrain yourself
in front of a feast?

60
00:11:10,005 --> 00:11:11,175
I can if I have to.

61
00:11:12,275 --> 00:11:13,575
I can do anything...

62
00:11:14,815 --> 00:11:16,145
for my health.

63
00:11:17,845 --> 00:11:20,015
We cleanse ourselves
of worldly dust and attachments.

64
00:11:20,255 --> 00:11:24,455
We pray to the sky and the earth.

65
00:11:24,725 --> 00:11:30,265
From the Muryangsa Temple

66
00:11:31,065 --> 00:11:33,735
Here in this world of suffering

67
00:11:33,795 --> 00:11:37,365
In Seodaemun District, Seoul, South Korea,

68
00:11:37,635 --> 00:11:42,405
In this pure sanctuary of Suwol

69
00:11:42,905 --> 00:11:48,215
At the request of
the humble devotee Ha Jae In

70
00:11:48,475 --> 00:11:51,545
We pray for the spirit
of the dearly departed Geum Ba Ra

71
00:11:51,545 --> 00:11:53,285
For the spirit of the dearly departed
Geum Ba Ra

72
00:11:53,455 --> 00:11:57,225
For the spirit of the dearly departed
Geum Ba Ra

73
00:11:57,425 --> 00:11:58,785
May she attain rebirth in paradise...

74
00:12:11,735 --> 00:12:12,735
Let go...

75
00:12:13,735 --> 00:12:15,335
of all earthly attachments...

76
00:12:16,075 --> 00:12:17,145
and depart in peace.

77
00:12:39,065 --> 00:12:40,065
Thank you.

78
00:12:47,605 --> 00:12:51,275
Drive safe.
I'll treat you to a meal sometime soon.

79
00:12:51,775 --> 00:12:52,775
Sure.

80
00:13:01,315 --> 00:13:02,985
She's really changed, that Momo.

81
00:13:07,825 --> 00:13:10,495
Such a waste of a pretty face
and a sharp mind.

82
00:13:10,795 --> 00:13:12,835
She must have studied so incredibly hard.

83
00:13:13,265 --> 00:13:15,135
And she never even had
one proper tutoring session.

84
00:13:15,265 --> 00:13:16,665
If she had married me,

85
00:13:20,435 --> 00:13:21,735
she wouldn't have died.

86
00:13:22,035 --> 00:13:24,705
Life and death are up to fate.
Her time was just up.

87
00:13:44,825 --> 00:13:45,825
Goodness.

88
00:13:47,895 --> 00:13:49,535
Did my little one burp?

89
00:13:51,005 --> 00:13:52,135
You're so adorable.

90
00:13:58,905 --> 00:14:00,315
Your Daddy...

91
00:14:02,445 --> 00:14:04,045
cried so much today.

92
00:14:13,595 --> 00:14:14,695
Thank you.

93
00:14:15,925 --> 00:14:17,365
I hope you find peace...

94
00:14:18,695 --> 00:14:19,935
wherever you are.

95
00:15:15,215 --> 00:15:16,955
I'd like to pour you a drink.

96
00:15:37,605 --> 00:15:38,645
You've been through so much.

97
00:15:38,775 --> 00:15:39,945
You're the one who has.

98
00:15:40,915 --> 00:15:41,945
Thank you so much.

99
00:15:47,915 --> 00:15:49,055
Just take a sip.

100
00:16:01,565 --> 00:16:03,105
When are you going to tell Yong Joong?

101
00:16:05,865 --> 00:16:07,835
- You're not going to tell him?
- No.

102
00:16:07,905 --> 00:16:08,905
Why?

103
00:16:09,875 --> 00:16:11,945
They already decided
to go their separate ways.

104
00:16:12,245 --> 00:16:13,715
Then why did you ask me for the surgery?

105
00:16:14,445 --> 00:16:15,445
Just because.

106
00:16:17,645 --> 00:16:20,115
I'm a better fit for Momo than Jin Ju is.

107
00:16:23,585 --> 00:16:24,685
That's the only reason?

108
00:16:29,025 --> 00:16:30,665
Yong Joong is having such a hard time.

109
00:16:33,835 --> 00:16:34,865
Are you punishing him?

110
00:16:35,595 --> 00:16:36,865
I'll explain everything to him.

111
00:16:37,135 --> 00:16:38,265
It's not the right thing to do.

112
00:16:38,335 --> 00:16:39,735
We're way past doing the right thing.

113
00:16:40,835 --> 00:16:42,275
He and Momo just had a falling out.

114
00:16:42,275 --> 00:16:44,645
Saying it's me would just confuse him.

115
00:16:45,675 --> 00:16:47,775
He'd have to force his feelings
all over again.

116
00:16:51,245 --> 00:16:52,245
It's up to you.

117
00:16:53,285 --> 00:16:55,215
I feel bad for Jin Ju.

118
00:17:08,535 --> 00:17:11,605
- Isn't there some way I can repay her?
- Of course there is.

119
00:17:13,535 --> 00:17:14,735
You'll be a fine replacement.

120
00:17:17,745 --> 00:17:18,805
I'm just kidding.

121
00:17:20,215 --> 00:17:21,675
I had a baby.

122
00:17:23,745 --> 00:17:24,745
A son.

123
00:17:38,865 --> 00:17:39,995
Did they move?

124
00:17:48,505 --> 00:17:49,505
Hello.

125
00:17:53,315 --> 00:17:55,515
- Who is that?
- Excuse me?

126
00:17:55,745 --> 00:17:57,015
It's...

127
00:17:57,785 --> 00:17:59,185
Ba Ra's baby.

128
00:18:00,115 --> 00:18:01,315
What brings you here?

129
00:18:01,785 --> 00:18:04,755
- Excuse me?
- Security didn't alert me.

130
00:18:05,485 --> 00:18:06,795
How did you get in here?

131
00:18:14,665 --> 00:18:16,295
Wait, is that my key?

132
00:18:17,235 --> 00:18:19,035
You don't remember giving it to me?

133
00:18:19,705 --> 00:18:20,735
Momo gave it to you?

134
00:18:23,975 --> 00:18:25,005
Who are you?

135
00:18:27,815 --> 00:18:29,115
Are you playing dumb?

136
00:18:31,945 --> 00:18:32,945
The key...

137
00:18:34,315 --> 00:18:35,855
Did you get it from Momo?

138
00:18:42,755 --> 00:18:43,995
Give me the key and leave.

139
00:18:45,225 --> 00:18:46,425
Call security.

140
00:19:03,785 --> 00:19:04,845
Who was that?

141
00:19:16,225 --> 00:19:18,425
(Kim Gwang Cheol)

142
00:19:20,135 --> 00:19:21,765
(Message: Kim Gwang Cheol)

143
00:19:24,205 --> 00:19:26,735
Are you on a trip?
Aren't you worried about your old man?

144
00:19:27,075 --> 00:19:28,335
I had surgery for stomach cancer.

145
00:19:30,345 --> 00:19:33,005
To get away from her father,
Jin Ju used me...

146
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:07,245
That little...

147
00:20:08,745 --> 00:20:10,915
She swapped bodies with Geum Ba Ra.

148
00:20:15,985 --> 00:20:17,725
(CCTV recording in progress)

149
00:20:24,165 --> 00:20:25,995
Is the owner of this house...

150
00:20:26,465 --> 00:20:27,965
still not out of the hospital yet?

151
00:20:28,435 --> 00:20:31,035
- Who are you?
- She's friends with my daughter.

152
00:20:31,105 --> 00:20:32,105
But you haven't heard?

153
00:20:32,765 --> 00:20:34,105
She passed away a little while ago.

154
00:20:36,235 --> 00:20:38,505
- In a car accident?
- No.

155
00:20:39,045 --> 00:20:40,775
Apparently, something went wrong
with her brain surgery.

156
00:20:41,515 --> 00:20:42,775
I can't believe it either.

157
00:20:58,965 --> 00:21:00,195
Kim Jin Ju.

158
00:21:01,365 --> 00:21:03,265
Stabbing me in the back
until the very end...

159
00:21:38,335 --> 00:21:41,805
(Like father, like daughter...)

160
00:22:05,495 --> 00:22:07,765
Evil can never triumph over good.

161
00:22:09,335 --> 00:22:11,635
Even a single ray of light
can illuminate the darkness.

162
00:22:12,605 --> 00:22:14,975
But no matter how much you try
to shroud the light in darkness,

163
00:22:15,705 --> 00:22:17,645
you can never blot it out.

164
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:51,175
I'm not sure...

165
00:22:53,005 --> 00:22:55,375
how I'm supposed to address you.

166
00:22:57,245 --> 00:23:00,555
The shelf collapsed,
and a diary accidentally fell open.

167
00:23:01,385 --> 00:23:02,585
The name...

168
00:23:03,285 --> 00:23:05,755
Hyun Ran Hee, Momo's mother,
caught my eye.

169
00:23:07,555 --> 00:23:09,295
Let me get straight to the point.

170
00:23:11,095 --> 00:23:13,265
The long-lost daughter
you've been searching for...

171
00:23:14,365 --> 00:23:15,465
is me,

172
00:23:16,195 --> 00:23:17,465
Geum Ba Ra.

173
00:23:20,135 --> 00:23:21,675
In one of the album photos,

174
00:23:22,405 --> 00:23:26,545
I saw a woman
who I thought looked a lot like me...

175
00:23:26,775 --> 00:23:28,845
and could've been an aunt.

176
00:23:29,715 --> 00:23:33,345
On the off-chance, I found a toothbrush,
a comb, and some hair,

177
00:23:33,855 --> 00:23:35,915
and I sent them for a DNA test.

178
00:23:37,485 --> 00:23:38,985
It came back as a match.

179
00:23:39,885 --> 00:23:41,995
I couldn't believe it,
so I checked again and again.

180
00:23:42,555 --> 00:23:45,095
Seeing the undeniable result,
I burst into tears.

181
00:23:46,595 --> 00:23:47,595
Father.

182
00:23:48,335 --> 00:23:49,335
Dad.

183
00:23:50,835 --> 00:23:51,835
"Dad."

184
00:23:52,905 --> 00:23:54,235
It's something...

185
00:23:55,235 --> 00:23:58,105
I've missed and desperately longed to say.

186
00:23:59,745 --> 00:24:00,945
So please...

187
00:24:02,315 --> 00:24:03,745
don't blame yourself anymore.

188
00:24:06,515 --> 00:24:08,015
I had a baby,

189
00:24:08,555 --> 00:24:09,555
a son.

190
00:24:11,185 --> 00:24:13,555
I ate the sea bream seaweed soup
that you made...

191
00:24:15,395 --> 00:24:17,565
with tears of joy.

192
00:24:18,995 --> 00:24:21,295
And thanks to you,
I've recovered well from childbirth.

193
00:24:23,395 --> 00:24:25,205
I'm so relieved and happy...

194
00:24:25,705 --> 00:24:28,435
to know who my mother...

195
00:24:29,205 --> 00:24:30,375
and father were...

196
00:24:31,205 --> 00:24:32,375
before I leave.

197
00:24:35,315 --> 00:24:36,575
I have no regrets.

198
00:24:37,745 --> 00:24:39,315
Please forgive me...

199
00:24:40,015 --> 00:24:42,755
for leaving without seeing you...

200
00:24:43,185 --> 00:24:44,455
or giving you one last hug.

201
00:24:45,325 --> 00:24:47,025
Please, try to accept this.

202
00:24:48,325 --> 00:24:52,365
Still, we met a few times,
so we'll always have those memories.

203
00:24:53,295 --> 00:24:55,195
Knowing that you're my father,

204
00:24:55,865 --> 00:24:58,005
I'm so happy.

205
00:24:58,605 --> 00:24:59,835
So very happy.

206
00:25:02,705 --> 00:25:03,945
Looking at your paintings,

207
00:25:04,805 --> 00:25:06,375
my heart and my soul...

208
00:25:07,145 --> 00:25:09,275
were filled with tears of love.

209
00:25:11,145 --> 00:25:13,315
I knew exactly what you were feeling
when you painted them,

210
00:25:13,885 --> 00:25:15,285
and it truly moved me.

211
00:25:17,185 --> 00:25:19,455
Because I have always felt the same way.

212
00:25:21,455 --> 00:25:24,665
Momo will explain the rest.

213
00:25:25,195 --> 00:25:28,935
Please consider Momo
as your second daughter.

214
00:25:30,765 --> 00:25:32,605
I respect you as an artist,

215
00:25:33,905 --> 00:25:35,675
and I love you as my father.

216
00:26:01,235 --> 00:26:02,435
How did this happen?

217
00:26:07,475 --> 00:26:09,635
Did you know she was your sister?

218
00:26:13,745 --> 00:26:14,745
Yes.

219
00:26:18,215 --> 00:26:20,515
I heard what happened to the reporter,
Geum Ba Ra.

220
00:26:24,185 --> 00:26:27,625
You see, I actually met her
before my daughter did.

221
00:26:27,895 --> 00:26:29,995
Things like this make you think
there's no deity.

222
00:26:30,665 --> 00:26:32,295
Of all the people to take...

223
00:26:33,735 --> 00:26:35,735
Was it really a cerebral hemorrhage?

224
00:26:37,065 --> 00:26:38,265
Yes.

225
00:26:38,465 --> 00:26:40,105
She seemed perfectly fine.

226
00:26:42,035 --> 00:26:45,105
Then, that girl is gone for good.

227
00:26:47,175 --> 00:26:48,315
Could I get some water?

228
00:27:01,825 --> 00:27:03,395
Who performed the surgery?

229
00:27:04,325 --> 00:27:05,765
Director Shin Ju Shin?

230
00:27:06,995 --> 00:27:07,995
Yes.

231
00:27:08,865 --> 00:27:10,765
They were both in their prime.
It's such a senseless loss.

232
00:27:11,865 --> 00:27:14,835
A part of me wonders if Jin Ju was lonely
and decided to take her along.

233
00:27:22,775 --> 00:27:25,245
He's your one and only grandson.

234
00:27:27,415 --> 00:27:28,455
What's his name?

235
00:27:33,425 --> 00:27:34,725
(Exam Room One,
Neurosurgery Director Shin Ju Shin)

236
00:27:50,405 --> 00:27:53,075
Please, I'm terrified of my dad.

237
00:27:53,715 --> 00:27:54,715
Please...

238
00:27:54,845 --> 00:27:55,975
I want to try...

239
00:27:56,845 --> 00:27:58,345
living as Momo.

240
00:28:30,445 --> 00:28:33,585
Where is Director Shin?
He's not answering his phone.

241
00:28:55,005 --> 00:28:56,375
Your husband is here.

242
00:29:09,015 --> 00:29:10,015
The baby.

243
00:29:17,995 --> 00:29:19,725
Why were both of your phones turned off?

244
00:29:22,335 --> 00:29:24,035
You haven't cleared out Ba Ra's place yet,
have you?

245
00:29:29,075 --> 00:29:30,075
I'll take care of it.

246
00:29:30,905 --> 00:29:32,445
She asked me to.

247
00:29:34,115 --> 00:29:35,775
Even so,
can you clear out her entire place?

248
00:29:36,675 --> 00:29:37,785
You don't have time for that.

249
00:29:38,045 --> 00:29:39,115
I can make time.

250
00:29:40,615 --> 00:29:41,785
Do you have time?

251
00:29:44,455 --> 00:29:45,825
Do you have time?

252
00:29:50,925 --> 00:29:51,925
Who is that?

253
00:29:52,295 --> 00:29:53,465
My manager.

254
00:29:54,295 --> 00:29:55,465
Planning a comeback?

255
00:29:56,095 --> 00:29:58,865
No, I just need someone to help me out.

256
00:30:01,475 --> 00:30:02,975
Why are you so down?

257
00:30:03,805 --> 00:30:06,005
I thought deep down
you'd be happy about this.

258
00:30:08,045 --> 00:30:09,715
You never felt this way about her.

259
00:30:15,285 --> 00:30:17,055
Ba Ra's door code.

260
00:30:19,385 --> 00:30:20,725
I'm going to buy the apartment...

261
00:30:21,325 --> 00:30:22,625
and use it as my studio.

262
00:30:38,575 --> 00:30:39,905
It's 1210, star.

263
00:30:45,345 --> 00:30:46,985
Is that the code Ba Ra set?

264
00:30:50,725 --> 00:30:52,185
That's my birthday...

265
00:31:09,475 --> 00:31:10,675
Is there someone in there?

266
00:31:13,445 --> 00:31:14,445
No.

267
00:31:22,385 --> 00:31:23,855
I'm going to do what I have to do.

268
00:31:49,345 --> 00:31:50,345
Yong Joong must be...

269
00:31:50,945 --> 00:31:51,945
the dad.

270
00:32:11,365 --> 00:32:13,065
(Yong Joong)

271
00:32:35,495 --> 00:32:36,625
How did you get in here?

272
00:32:43,235 --> 00:32:45,065
You're supposed to wear a swimsuit
at the pool.

273
00:32:47,375 --> 00:32:49,275
Jin Ju's father came to see me.

274
00:32:52,145 --> 00:32:54,575
She proposed the surgery
just to get away from her father.

275
00:32:55,045 --> 00:32:56,875
I saw a 300,000 dollar transfer
in her account.

276
00:32:56,875 --> 00:32:58,115
Sounds just like Kim Jin Ju.

277
00:32:59,845 --> 00:33:01,685
It's true what they say,
people don't change.

278
00:33:02,785 --> 00:33:04,425
I had no idea.

279
00:33:05,355 --> 00:33:07,125
All this time, I just felt sorry for her.

280
00:33:08,695 --> 00:33:11,025
Looks like you already know who I am,

281
00:33:11,965 --> 00:33:13,425
seeing how you haven't asked.

282
00:33:15,565 --> 00:33:17,905
My daughter gave me your number.

283
00:33:17,965 --> 00:33:21,135
She said you, Director Shin Ju Shin,
with your world-shocking skills,

284
00:33:21,635 --> 00:33:23,905
made her into Momo.

285
00:33:26,145 --> 00:33:27,515
So what did you do with her body?

286
00:33:29,345 --> 00:33:30,445
My daughter's body.

287
00:33:31,985 --> 00:33:34,185
- Jin Ju.
- Please, have a seat.

288
00:33:45,095 --> 00:33:46,265
Answer me.

289
00:33:46,895 --> 00:33:49,335
If you put her brain in Momo's body,

290
00:33:50,195 --> 00:33:51,935
what did you do with her body?

291
00:33:53,935 --> 00:33:54,935
I don't know.

292
00:33:56,435 --> 00:33:58,445
- You don't know?
- I just did the surgery.

293
00:33:59,675 --> 00:34:00,675
My staff handled it.

294
00:34:03,275 --> 00:34:04,485
Who on your staff?

295
00:34:05,485 --> 00:34:06,485
Give me a name.

296
00:34:09,385 --> 00:34:11,755
You threw her away as medical waste,
didn't you?

297
00:34:12,325 --> 00:34:13,455
Where?

298
00:34:18,865 --> 00:34:20,795
I noticed Momo was different again.

299
00:34:21,995 --> 00:34:22,995
Who is it this time?

300
00:34:27,005 --> 00:34:28,105
Aren't you going to answer me?

301
00:34:32,545 --> 00:34:34,275
Is it Reporter Geum Ba Ra?

302
00:34:37,515 --> 00:34:39,985
You swapped their brains again.

303
00:34:41,385 --> 00:34:45,155
Is my daughter, Kim Jin Ju, dead?

304
00:34:45,555 --> 00:34:46,825
For good?

305
00:34:48,455 --> 00:34:49,855
Is she dead?

306
00:35:56,125 --> 00:35:57,695
My daughter!

307
00:36:30,825 --> 00:36:32,095
He's stabbing the Director!

308
00:40:38,175 --> 00:40:39,275
Ba Ra.

309
00:40:48,185 --> 00:40:49,185
Geum Ba Ra.

310
00:40:57,495 --> 00:41:00,595
(Nua General Hospital)

311
00:41:02,095 --> 00:41:05,205
The person you've called is unavailable.
Please leave a message after the tone.

312
00:41:05,265 --> 00:41:07,005
(Director Shin Ju Shin)

313
00:41:07,105 --> 00:41:11,875
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

314
00:41:12,875 --> 00:41:14,875
- Is the Director...
- He must be sick.

315
00:41:14,945 --> 00:41:16,875
- He's not in yet?
- No.

316
00:41:51,915 --> 00:41:55,485
Hello? This is the 21st floor
of Nua General Hospital.

317
00:41:55,555 --> 00:41:56,985
There's a dead body here!

318
00:42:00,255 --> 00:42:03,355
(Nua General Hospital)

319
00:42:09,865 --> 00:42:12,535
I think it's a patient
we operated on recently.

320
00:42:12,605 --> 00:42:14,735
- And the Director isn't here?
- No, sir.

321
00:42:28,985 --> 00:42:29,985
You...

322
00:42:38,195 --> 00:42:39,365
No.

323
00:42:43,595 --> 00:42:45,235
Nurse Lee! Don't!

324
00:43:02,715 --> 00:43:03,915
Director Shin!

325
00:43:25,575 --> 00:43:27,075
He kept grilling me with questions.

326
00:43:27,075 --> 00:43:28,545
"Did Geum Ba Ra have brain surgery?"

327
00:43:28,615 --> 00:43:30,015
"Did Director Shin perform
the surgery himself?"

328
00:43:31,985 --> 00:43:33,845
What if he wasn't
Kim Jin Ju's biological father,

329
00:43:33,915 --> 00:43:35,115
but Ba Ra's instead?

330
00:43:37,485 --> 00:43:40,555
There's no other reason
he'd snap and kill him like that.

331
00:43:45,565 --> 00:43:48,495
(Our deepest condolences to the family,
The Staff of Nua Funeral Home)

332
00:44:00,045 --> 00:44:01,745
You'll live longer
with a little imperfection.

333
00:44:02,145 --> 00:44:03,675
And I take it you don't, Director Shin?

334
00:44:04,415 --> 00:44:05,585
I guess I'm not long for this world, then.

335
00:44:13,955 --> 00:44:15,495
I didn't see it myself,

336
00:44:17,625 --> 00:44:18,625
but at home...

337
00:44:50,495 --> 00:44:53,565
Border Collies, Jindo dogs,
Chow Chows, Tibetan Mastiffs...

338
00:44:54,095 --> 00:44:55,795
You can have all the dogs you want,

339
00:44:55,795 --> 00:44:58,365
and we can live here, together.

340
00:44:58,505 --> 00:45:01,065
I'm always grateful. I really am.

341
00:45:01,135 --> 00:45:02,505
Then get rid of that feeling,
starting now.

342
00:45:03,675 --> 00:45:05,075
I'm not lacking for anything,

343
00:45:06,145 --> 00:45:07,505
and I'm tired of being thanked.

344
00:45:08,145 --> 00:45:10,375
I don't care for effort
born from obligation.

345
00:45:10,845 --> 00:45:12,285
I'm not forcing myself.

346
00:45:12,715 --> 00:45:13,715
Regardless.

347
00:45:15,955 --> 00:45:17,615
Want me to look for a purebred Retriever?

348
00:45:24,125 --> 00:45:25,365
You transferred 300,000 dollars.

349
00:45:25,895 --> 00:45:27,565
- That's right.
- Were you being blackmailed?

350
00:45:27,625 --> 00:45:30,365
No. Why would I be blackmailed?

351
00:45:30,735 --> 00:45:33,835
He said he didn't know how to go on
after Jin Ju died.

352
00:45:34,535 --> 00:45:36,605
Jin Ju was always really good to me.

353
00:45:37,035 --> 00:45:39,145
I sent it to him
as a sort of severance package.

354
00:45:39,475 --> 00:45:40,545
But 300,000 dollars?

355
00:45:40,745 --> 00:45:41,745
Yes.

356
00:45:43,145 --> 00:45:46,545
He said he couldn't get a job anywhere
because of his record.

357
00:45:58,025 --> 00:46:00,525
We had so many memories together
in this house.

358
00:46:01,895 --> 00:46:04,395
All those meals your mother made
for us here.

359
00:46:06,065 --> 00:46:09,175
You'd hate this house going to another.
I know I would.

360
00:46:12,945 --> 00:46:14,175
Did you meet Ba Ra?

361
00:46:17,845 --> 00:46:19,085
Of course you did.

362
00:46:23,415 --> 00:46:25,155
("Fearless Love")

363
00:46:49,015 --> 00:46:50,815
("Fearless Love")

364
00:46:52,745 --> 00:46:53,745
(Momo)

365
00:46:58,115 --> 00:46:59,125
Hello.

366
00:46:59,385 --> 00:47:01,795
Are you just going to neglect
Yong Joong like that?

367
00:47:03,125 --> 00:47:06,925
Did you know he moved
into Reporter Geum's apartment?

368
00:47:09,565 --> 00:47:11,735
Reporter Geum is gone,
Director Shin is gone...

369
00:47:12,065 --> 00:47:13,505
Now it's just the two of you.

370
00:47:14,235 --> 00:47:15,705
You only have each other now.

371
00:47:19,245 --> 00:47:22,975
Men have a certain kind of pride
that women can't understand...

372
00:47:23,075 --> 00:47:25,915
And women don't? We have our pride too.

373
00:47:26,385 --> 00:47:28,255
Just think of her as his first love.

374
00:47:29,515 --> 00:47:32,625
He's a good guy with a big heart,
so he can't just let her go easily.

375
00:47:33,685 --> 00:47:35,225
Even though you're younger,

376
00:47:35,755 --> 00:47:37,825
be the bigger person and take care of him.

377
00:47:38,465 --> 00:47:39,765
Tell him you want to make things work.

378
00:47:40,365 --> 00:47:42,895
He'll be so grateful,
he'll be the most loyal husband ever.

379
00:47:43,365 --> 00:47:44,435
I guarantee it.

380
00:48:36,315 --> 00:48:37,355
Yong Joong.

381
00:48:38,555 --> 00:48:39,785
Don't let this get you down.

382
00:48:54,165 --> 00:48:55,175
Ba Ra.

383
00:49:05,645 --> 00:49:06,645
(James)

384
00:49:10,085 --> 00:49:12,025
- Hey.
- Where are you? Home?

385
00:49:12,425 --> 00:49:14,225
- No.
- You are not going to believe this.

386
00:49:14,355 --> 00:49:16,295
I'm on my way to your house,
so run there...

387
00:49:16,655 --> 00:49:17,725
at the speed of light.

388
00:49:56,565 --> 00:49:58,535
I wonder if Paul Kim has arrived yet.

389
00:50:07,505 --> 00:50:08,615
(Artist Paul Kim)

390
00:50:12,445 --> 00:50:14,315
Hello, Mr. Ha.

391
00:50:14,615 --> 00:50:15,615
Hello.

392
00:50:16,185 --> 00:50:18,455
Are you still in Germany?

393
00:50:18,955 --> 00:50:19,955
No, I'm back.

394
00:50:20,855 --> 00:50:21,855
When did you get back?

395
00:50:23,755 --> 00:50:25,195
Do I hear a baby crying?

396
00:50:26,565 --> 00:50:27,565
It's my grandson.

397
00:50:28,835 --> 00:50:29,835
Your grandson?

398
00:50:30,135 --> 00:50:31,265
I found my daughter.

399
00:50:33,005 --> 00:50:35,735
But it's a long story.

400
00:50:35,935 --> 00:50:37,475
You were bound to find out anyway.

401
00:50:38,335 --> 00:50:40,205
I'm at Momo's place right now.

402
00:50:43,115 --> 00:50:45,445
You're saying Reporter Geum Ba Ra
was your long-lost daughter?

403
00:50:46,145 --> 00:50:47,145
Yes.

404
00:50:52,055 --> 00:50:53,785
At least she had the baby
before she passed away.

405
00:50:54,325 --> 00:50:56,825
So the baby's mother is Reporter Geum?

406
00:50:57,625 --> 00:50:58,625
Yes.

407
00:50:59,795 --> 00:51:01,025
Is it a boy or a girl?

408
00:51:02,395 --> 00:51:04,465
- It's a boy.
- When was he born?

409
00:51:04,695 --> 00:51:05,865
He's almost three months old.

410
00:51:08,535 --> 00:51:09,635
And who's the father?

411
00:51:10,175 --> 00:51:11,175
I don't know.

412
00:51:17,645 --> 00:51:18,685
Go and have your dinner.

413
00:51:22,415 --> 00:51:24,155
So you didn't know
anything about it either?

414
00:51:27,425 --> 00:51:28,425
What is it?

415
00:51:28,795 --> 00:51:29,795
Goodness.

416
00:51:32,225 --> 00:51:34,195
He's your son, no doubt about it.

417
00:51:34,195 --> 00:51:38,195
He's a carbon copy of you
when you were a baby.

418
00:51:38,195 --> 00:51:40,205
Did he really say Ba Ra had a baby?

419
00:51:40,205 --> 00:51:41,335
Yes.

420
00:51:41,335 --> 00:51:42,405
The situation...

421
00:51:42,835 --> 00:51:46,475
I mean, Reporter Geum and Momo
are half-sisters who share a mother.

422
00:51:48,275 --> 00:51:49,415
I've never seen anything like this.

423
00:51:49,615 --> 00:51:51,645
You don't even need a DNA test.

424
00:51:52,545 --> 00:51:54,215
She must have disappeared
after she found out she was pregnant.

425
00:51:55,315 --> 00:51:56,715
Poor Reporter Geum...

426
00:51:56,715 --> 00:51:57,985
How could she die...

427
00:51:58,385 --> 00:52:00,055
and leave her newborn?

428
00:52:09,335 --> 00:52:10,795
We have to bring him here and raise him.

429
00:52:10,795 --> 00:52:13,165
I know it sounds like a soap opera,

430
00:52:13,235 --> 00:52:14,235
Reporter Geum, Momo...

431
00:52:14,505 --> 00:52:18,875
I told Momo to get back with you
because she seemed different.

432
00:52:20,775 --> 00:52:21,775
Are you going to see for yourself?

433
00:52:23,145 --> 00:52:24,575
Let's go together. We'll take my car.

434
00:52:25,345 --> 00:52:26,415
You've already seen him.

435
00:52:27,945 --> 00:52:29,185
I want to see him again.

436
00:52:34,255 --> 00:52:36,255
They say the world is big and small,

437
00:52:36,255 --> 00:52:38,665
but who would've thought it was Paul Kim?

438
00:52:40,195 --> 00:52:42,435
He spent all that time
desperately searching for his daughter.

439
00:52:46,105 --> 00:52:49,105
Poor Reporter Geum,
and the baby, of course.

440
00:52:50,135 --> 00:52:51,235
This is crazy...

441
00:53:00,315 --> 00:53:02,215
It's not something
that needs to be a secret.

442
00:53:02,655 --> 00:53:04,085
He asked whose baby it was,

443
00:53:04,715 --> 00:53:05,985
and there was no reason to lie.

444
00:53:07,225 --> 00:53:08,225
Right.

445
00:53:10,755 --> 00:53:12,725
You should've seen
how shocked he looked...

446
00:53:13,665 --> 00:53:14,665
after seeing the baby.

447
00:53:15,365 --> 00:53:17,195
I guess he never saw it coming?

448
00:53:18,805 --> 00:53:20,365
I had no idea we would end up
connected like this,

449
00:53:21,105 --> 00:53:23,435
and I've been pretty close
with James Ha this whole time.

450
00:53:26,175 --> 00:53:27,305
I should have introduced myself sooner.

451
00:53:28,045 --> 00:53:29,075
I'm Ha Yong Joong.

452
00:53:30,215 --> 00:53:32,245
- You don't have to...
- Take it.

453
00:53:35,415 --> 00:53:36,655
Sorry to bother you so late.

454
00:53:37,215 --> 00:53:38,625
How about some rooibos tea?

455
00:53:38,755 --> 00:53:40,725
No, I'm fine.
I don't feel like having anything.

456
00:53:41,155 --> 00:53:42,155
Please, have a seat.

457
00:53:46,495 --> 00:53:47,495
Is the baby asleep?

458
00:53:47,765 --> 00:53:50,635
- He's having some formula.
- Eat and sleep, that's all he does.

459
00:53:51,565 --> 00:53:53,035
He's not awake for very long.

460
00:53:53,265 --> 00:53:55,605
He probably won't start crawling
until he's 8 or 9 months old.

461
00:53:59,475 --> 00:54:01,945
So you were close with my daughter too?

462
00:54:08,655 --> 00:54:09,655
Yes.

463
00:54:18,255 --> 00:54:19,265
Hello?

464
00:54:20,265 --> 00:54:21,265
Really?

465
00:54:23,135 --> 00:54:24,135
Thank you.

466
00:54:25,805 --> 00:54:28,105
I'll be home in a bit. Yes.

467
00:54:32,275 --> 00:54:34,545
That was a neighbor,
saying the lights are on at my house.

468
00:54:35,775 --> 00:54:37,145
I was so excited to see my grandson...

469
00:54:37,745 --> 00:54:39,115
that I rushed out, leaving the lights on.

470
00:54:40,385 --> 00:54:42,455
Could you please explain
in a bit more detail?

471
00:54:42,915 --> 00:54:44,255
What exactly happened?

472
00:54:53,125 --> 00:54:54,125
Not now.

473
00:54:57,135 --> 00:54:59,935
Honestly, it still doesn't feel real.

474
00:55:08,545 --> 00:55:10,645
There's this letter,

475
00:55:11,445 --> 00:55:12,845
and the DNA test results.

476
00:55:21,885 --> 00:55:23,355
Is that Reporter Geum's hair?

477
00:55:24,555 --> 00:55:25,565
Yes.

478
00:55:26,465 --> 00:55:29,065
- Couldn't it have been malpractice?
- No.

479
00:55:30,135 --> 00:55:33,005
Director Shin Ju Shin is
a leading authority on brain surgery.

480
00:55:33,835 --> 00:55:34,965
That is true.

481
00:55:38,175 --> 00:55:41,905
I'll be sure to come by
and pay my respects properly soon.

482
00:55:45,915 --> 00:55:48,415
In any case, we're officially family now.

483
00:55:49,085 --> 00:55:50,085
I suppose we are.

484
00:55:50,455 --> 00:55:53,325
I'll set something up for us all
to get together properly.

485
00:57:55,515 --> 00:57:56,775
He's your son, right?

486
00:58:00,685 --> 00:58:02,715
It's not right for him
to be living with his aunt.

487
00:58:03,055 --> 00:58:04,455
We should be the ones raising him.

488
00:58:05,885 --> 00:58:07,385
When Momo finds out everything,

489
00:58:07,925 --> 00:58:08,995
think about Paul Kim...

490
00:58:10,725 --> 00:58:12,365
It's something I have
to face sooner or later.

491
00:58:15,265 --> 00:58:16,995
Before we officially started dating,

492
00:58:19,905 --> 00:58:21,435
I spent one night with Ba Ra.

493
00:58:23,835 --> 00:58:25,305
I didn't know she got pregnant,

494
00:58:27,005 --> 00:58:29,275
and I think she left
because of a misunderstanding.

495
00:58:31,875 --> 00:58:32,885
What misunderstanding?

496
00:58:33,815 --> 00:58:34,915
It's hard to explain.

497
00:58:37,185 --> 00:58:39,185
It's just putting your thoughts
into words.

498
00:58:39,655 --> 00:58:40,655
Is it that hard?

499
00:58:43,395 --> 00:58:44,495
Ba Ra is the one who needs to hear it.

500
00:58:46,825 --> 00:58:47,825
But she's not here, is she?

501
00:58:52,435 --> 00:58:54,405
We met again after 15 years
for an interview.

502
00:58:56,875 --> 00:59:00,605
If I hadn't realized she was the kid
I knew growing up,

503
00:59:02,245 --> 00:59:04,775
we might have started dating.
Or at least, I think so.

504
00:59:07,615 --> 00:59:09,915
I could vaguely sense
a certain longing in her,

505
00:59:11,915 --> 00:59:13,425
but at the same time,
she was so self-assured.

506
00:59:15,185 --> 00:59:16,195
It was refreshing.

507
00:59:21,995 --> 00:59:22,995
Anyway,

508
00:59:24,435 --> 00:59:26,305
the next day,
I had to go on a business trip abroad,

509
00:59:29,405 --> 00:59:31,605
and I was hit with this feeling
that I'd done something terrible.

510
00:59:33,605 --> 00:59:35,575
I kept picturing Ba Ra's face
as a little girl,

511
00:59:36,775 --> 00:59:37,775
and I was so confused.

512
00:59:39,845 --> 00:59:41,545
I couldn't marry her
in that state of mind,

513
00:59:42,215 --> 00:59:43,685
so I asked her for some time.

514
00:59:47,885 --> 00:59:49,295
But I think she must have misunderstood.

515
00:59:57,035 --> 00:59:59,005
"Just another rejection."

516
01:00:00,665 --> 01:00:02,135
She must have thought that.

517
01:00:12,915 --> 01:00:14,045
I guess it's because you're sisters.

518
01:00:15,345 --> 01:00:17,115
It feels just like I'm talking to Ba Ra.

519
01:00:17,955 --> 01:00:19,285
I never noticed it before.

520
01:00:24,995 --> 01:00:25,995
So...

521
01:00:27,065 --> 01:00:28,795
we need to file the divorce papers
as planned.

522
01:00:29,595 --> 01:00:30,835
This isn't right.

523
01:00:33,165 --> 01:00:34,465
I'll raise Bi.

524
01:00:34,865 --> 01:00:36,175
She asked me to take care of him.

525
01:00:36,175 --> 01:00:37,705
He's better with his dad
than with his aunt.

526
01:00:38,575 --> 01:00:39,945
I'm confident I can raise him well.

527
01:00:39,945 --> 01:00:40,975
And let a stepmother raise him?

528
01:00:41,275 --> 01:00:43,375
I'm not getting married again to anyone.

529
01:00:49,055 --> 01:00:50,055
Just like how my brother...

530
01:00:50,885 --> 01:00:52,185
raised me...

531
01:00:53,455 --> 01:00:55,155
I'll make sure he never feels the void
of not having a mother.

532
01:00:56,495 --> 01:00:59,195
I'm confident I can raise him with love.

533
01:01:03,895 --> 01:01:04,895
Please.

534
01:01:07,765 --> 01:01:09,875
Honestly, I wasn't a very good husband.

535
01:01:13,645 --> 01:01:15,075
After his 100-day celebration,

536
01:01:15,975 --> 01:01:16,975
you can take him.

537
01:01:21,985 --> 01:01:22,985
Thank you.

538
01:01:23,455 --> 01:01:25,485
We'll file the papers after that.

539
01:01:35,495 --> 01:01:37,665
I'm going to register him as Geum Bi.

540
01:01:39,605 --> 01:01:41,905
Ha Geum Bi.

541
01:01:44,175 --> 01:01:46,275
Ha Geum Bi.

542
01:01:49,745 --> 01:01:52,245
- Hello.
- Right. This room...

543
01:01:52,245 --> 01:01:54,345
No, wait, in that room over there, please.

544
01:01:54,685 --> 01:01:55,685
Got it.

545
01:01:57,515 --> 01:01:59,225
Let's see, what else...

546
01:02:01,685 --> 01:02:03,455
Maybe I should've redone the wallpaper.

547
01:02:08,465 --> 01:02:09,935
It's not your fault, Yong Joong.

548
01:02:13,505 --> 01:02:16,475
It was probably from the shock
after his business failed,

549
01:02:18,135 --> 01:02:20,445
but my father also died of
a brain hemorrhage just eight days later.

550
01:02:26,615 --> 01:02:27,745
And I'm sure,

551
01:02:29,285 --> 01:02:30,515
Ba Ra didn't have any resentment.

552
01:02:32,785 --> 01:02:33,785
If anything,

553
01:02:34,825 --> 01:02:37,025
I think she was grateful.

554
01:02:48,865 --> 01:02:51,605
(I'm not sure
how I'm supposed to address you.)

555
01:02:54,875 --> 01:02:56,345
Still, you had it better than I did.

556
01:02:57,945 --> 01:03:00,845
I never got to see her grow up.

557
01:03:01,615 --> 01:03:03,415
Or even hold her hand once.

558
01:03:03,755 --> 01:03:04,755
All I got...

559
01:03:05,155 --> 01:03:08,685
was meeting her a few times
as an artist and a reporter.

560
01:03:11,125 --> 01:03:12,525
Why don't you come live with us?

561
01:03:17,335 --> 01:03:18,335
Whenever you're ready.

562
01:03:19,405 --> 01:03:22,235
I think having his grandfather around...

563
01:03:22,775 --> 01:03:24,235
would be so much better
for Geum Bi emotionally.

564
01:03:27,975 --> 01:03:30,645
- I'll visit often, if it's no trouble.
- Trouble? Of course not.

565
01:03:31,745 --> 01:03:33,145
You're my father-in-law.

566
01:03:35,045 --> 01:03:37,785
I'm curious about
how he and my mother met,

567
01:03:38,115 --> 01:03:39,425
but he won't tell me.

568
01:03:42,925 --> 01:03:43,925
You know, don't you?

569
01:03:44,455 --> 01:03:45,795
I heard you know the whole story.

570
01:03:45,865 --> 01:03:47,765
It's probably hard for him to tell you.

571
01:03:48,065 --> 01:03:49,795
It's not like they ended on good terms.

572
01:03:50,995 --> 01:03:52,195
But that's all in the past now.

573
01:03:55,565 --> 01:03:57,335
They met back in high school.

574
01:03:57,635 --> 01:03:59,845
CEO Hyun was a year older. She was 20.

575
01:04:00,575 --> 01:04:02,915
She dropped out of her freshman year
to have the baby.

576
01:04:03,645 --> 01:04:06,615
At the time, I think Paul's family
suddenly went bankrupt.

577
01:04:07,315 --> 01:04:10,015
Maybe that's why, but I heard
she left the baby and just disappeared.

578
01:04:11,155 --> 01:04:12,585
I don't know for sure,

579
01:04:12,785 --> 01:04:15,125
but he said even her mother
didn't know where she was.

580
01:04:16,825 --> 01:04:18,795
He said she was a newborn,
not even ten days old.

581
01:04:26,335 --> 01:04:29,675
If Reporter Geum were still with us,
you would be sisters again.

582
01:04:29,975 --> 01:04:31,405
It would be a perfect happy ending.

583
01:04:32,745 --> 01:04:34,175
But when I think of...

584
01:04:34,175 --> 01:04:36,345
Yong Joong and Geum Bi
spending their whole lives missing you...

585
01:04:37,145 --> 01:04:39,645
No matter how hard we all try,
no matter how well...

586
01:04:40,345 --> 01:04:41,815
we raise him,

587
01:04:42,345 --> 01:04:43,615
that void left by his mother...

588
01:04:44,755 --> 01:04:45,815
I know what that's like.

589
01:04:48,425 --> 01:04:51,395
The necklace I put on her,
engraved with her name and birthday,

590
01:04:52,295 --> 01:04:53,965
must have broken or fallen off,

591
01:04:54,325 --> 01:04:57,495
and ended up in Kim Gwang Cheol's
daughter's swaddling blanket.

592
01:04:58,365 --> 01:04:59,835
That's how they got switched.

593
01:05:00,705 --> 01:05:02,735
They were both taken to Minjin Church
on the same day.

594
01:05:08,005 --> 01:05:11,215
You could just raise Geum Bi together.

595
01:05:12,745 --> 01:05:15,145
It's not like the whole world knows
our family's private business.

596
01:05:16,655 --> 01:05:19,355
That kind of thing happened
from time to time back in the day.

597
01:05:24,895 --> 01:05:26,765
Ready? Smile!

598
01:05:27,725 --> 01:05:30,935
A bigger smile now. Show me your teeth.

599
01:05:30,935 --> 01:05:31,965
Look at you.

600
01:05:31,965 --> 01:05:35,665
Everyone, let's give Geum Bi a big hand!
One, two!

601
01:05:36,875 --> 01:05:38,675
Great. That looks very natural.

602
01:05:38,775 --> 01:05:42,275
(To my beloved baby,
May you grow up beautiful and healthy)

603
01:05:43,575 --> 01:05:45,985
The chef would like to know
how you're enjoying your meal.

604
01:05:46,545 --> 01:05:48,885
Please tell the chef it is excellent...

605
01:05:48,885 --> 01:05:50,655
- and thank him for the special care.
- I will.

606
01:05:51,515 --> 01:05:54,425
Next time, let's go somewhere more casual
so we can bring Geum Bi.

607
01:05:54,485 --> 01:05:57,525
That's right. So many decent places
don't allow kids these days.

608
01:05:58,255 --> 01:06:00,025
Mr. Kim, I'll get it next time.

609
01:06:00,965 --> 01:06:01,965
Sure.

610
01:06:04,235 --> 01:06:06,005
Now that you're leaving showbiz,
what's next?

611
01:06:06,665 --> 01:06:08,565
I took over the foundation
that runs the Nua Children's Home.

612
01:06:09,205 --> 01:06:10,205
Really?

613
01:06:10,205 --> 01:06:13,605
My goal is to identify the kids' talents
and help them cultivate their strengths.

614
01:06:15,845 --> 01:06:17,675
I can help teach painting.

615
01:06:18,345 --> 01:06:19,715
That would be amazing, thank you.

616
01:06:29,625 --> 01:06:32,595
My dear daughter,
don't you worry about Geum Bi.

617
01:06:40,165 --> 01:06:42,635
Excuse me, our ambassador is a big fan...

618
01:06:42,635 --> 01:06:44,675
and was hoping he could get a picture.

619
01:06:50,415 --> 01:06:52,945
- Of course.
- This is Ms. Momo's husband.

620
01:06:56,615 --> 01:06:58,915
I'm Yong Joong Ha.
It's an honor to meet you.

621
01:06:59,055 --> 01:07:01,855
No, no, the honor is mine.
You've made quite an impression.

622
01:07:02,355 --> 01:07:05,655
Thank you, Your Excellency.
You are the one who is truly impressive.

623
01:07:06,765 --> 01:07:09,325
Let me now introduce
a fashion industry leader.

624
01:07:09,865 --> 01:07:12,435
This is James Ha, CEO of Lim Company.

625
01:07:14,765 --> 01:07:15,835
Was it last year?

626
01:07:15,835 --> 01:07:17,705
I believe we met
at a party at the Egyptian embassy.

627
01:07:17,905 --> 01:07:19,235
Perhaps it was last year.

628
01:07:19,305 --> 01:07:21,645
I think we met at a party
at the Egyptian embassy.

629
01:07:21,745 --> 01:07:23,575
- Did we?
- Goodness.

630
01:07:23,715 --> 01:07:25,615
You both have such
an amazing sense of style.

631
01:07:25,675 --> 01:07:28,315
Both of you have such
a remarkable sense of style.

632
01:07:29,485 --> 01:07:31,085
- Thank you.
- You look stunning.

633
01:07:31,085 --> 01:07:32,855
I'll make sure to stop by sometime.

634
01:07:33,225 --> 01:07:35,255
She says she'll be sure
to stop by sometime.

635
01:07:35,385 --> 01:07:36,725
It would be my honor.

636
01:07:37,495 --> 01:07:38,525
Your Excellency,

637
01:07:38,825 --> 01:07:41,165
you had an interview
with Reporter Ba Ra Geum...

638
01:07:41,225 --> 01:07:42,965
from Sungwoo Daily last year, didn't you?

639
01:07:43,495 --> 01:07:45,365
How did you know that?
Did you read the article?

640
01:07:45,365 --> 01:07:46,405
Yes.

641
01:07:46,605 --> 01:07:50,105
I was so inspired by your interview,
so I saved a copy of it.

642
01:07:50,905 --> 01:07:51,905
I'm flattered.

643
01:07:52,335 --> 01:07:53,975
It's such an honor to meet you here.

644
01:07:54,405 --> 01:07:55,645
Shall we take a picture?

645
01:07:55,905 --> 01:07:56,915
Yes, sure.

646
01:07:57,715 --> 01:07:58,945
On the count of three.

647
01:07:58,945 --> 01:08:01,745
One, two, three.

648
01:08:02,615 --> 01:08:03,685
Big smile.

649
01:08:05,415 --> 01:08:06,425
Great.

650
01:08:09,155 --> 01:08:11,095
Climb up.

651
01:08:11,095 --> 01:08:12,555
One, two,

652
01:08:13,225 --> 01:08:14,495
three, four.

653
01:08:14,495 --> 01:08:16,995
And back, one, two, three, four.

654
01:08:17,065 --> 01:08:19,505
- That's how it's done, all right?
- Yes!

655
01:08:19,835 --> 01:08:22,235
Just keep working hard.
The sky helps those who help themselves.

656
01:08:22,735 --> 01:08:24,335
We just have to give it our all.

657
01:08:24,335 --> 01:08:25,335
- Okay.
- Okay.

658
01:08:25,335 --> 01:08:26,745
All right, let's take it from the top.

659
01:08:44,855 --> 01:08:46,825
She must've secretly studied English.

660
01:08:47,025 --> 01:08:48,265
I was completely surprised.

661
01:08:51,495 --> 01:08:54,205
Anyway, you've got to give her credit.
Her whole demeanor has changed.

662
01:08:54,365 --> 01:08:55,605
She's like a whole new person.

663
01:08:58,005 --> 01:09:00,045
Our little man is awake.

664
01:09:08,645 --> 01:09:10,515
(Yong Joong)

665
01:09:17,955 --> 01:09:20,065
(Yong Joong)

666
01:09:22,765 --> 01:09:23,765
Hello?

667
01:09:24,165 --> 01:09:25,595
I've got the papers ready.

668
01:09:26,035 --> 01:09:28,005
We should probably handle this
through our lawyers, right?

669
01:09:30,005 --> 01:09:31,735
It'll be all over the news anyway.

670
01:09:32,375 --> 01:09:33,545
Let's just go together.

671
01:09:34,405 --> 01:09:35,405
To the courthouse ourselves?

672
01:09:35,705 --> 01:09:36,745
Yes.

673
01:09:36,745 --> 01:09:37,975
All right.

674
01:09:38,515 --> 01:09:39,645
When are you free?

675
01:09:41,015 --> 01:09:42,015
Tomorrow...

676
01:09:43,285 --> 01:09:44,885
Let's file them after lunch.

677
01:09:46,285 --> 01:09:47,285
Okay.

678
01:10:21,355 --> 01:10:22,655
Isn't it hard running the orphanage?

679
01:10:23,355 --> 01:10:24,495
I mean, all you've ever done is act.

680
01:10:25,495 --> 01:10:26,795
Nothing in life is ever easy.

681
01:10:34,705 --> 01:10:36,135
The kids love it, though.

682
01:10:37,405 --> 01:10:38,705
You can see the change in their eyes.

683
01:10:51,185 --> 01:10:52,185
Enjoy your meal.

684
01:10:52,585 --> 01:10:53,585
Thank you.

685
01:10:55,855 --> 01:10:58,155
Are you really not going to act anymore?

686
01:10:59,555 --> 01:11:00,565
Yes.

687
01:11:00,565 --> 01:11:03,065
Your reruns have been on a lot lately.

688
01:11:03,535 --> 01:11:05,065
They never get old.

689
01:11:12,735 --> 01:11:13,745
You're not adding vinegar?

690
01:11:15,475 --> 01:11:16,475
No.

691
01:11:16,915 --> 01:11:18,275
Ba Ra eats hers plain, too.

692
01:11:22,385 --> 01:11:23,585
You two are definitely sisters.

693
01:11:24,285 --> 01:11:25,355
You even have the same taste in food.

694
01:11:43,975 --> 01:11:45,435
When I was pregnant with Geum Bi,

695
01:11:45,435 --> 01:11:47,475
I was craving these cold noodles.

696
01:11:49,745 --> 01:11:52,945
That's why I went to the cafe that day,
just on the off chance.

697
01:12:00,225 --> 01:12:01,925
And I wanted to see you, too.

698
01:12:09,625 --> 01:12:11,335
I really enjoyed the meal that day.

699
01:12:16,205 --> 01:12:17,405
You said if mine were too spicy,

700
01:12:19,105 --> 01:12:20,705
you'd let me have your cold noodles.

701
01:13:10,655 --> 01:13:13,725
(Geumnyeong-ro 42-gil 17)

702
01:15:15,345 --> 01:15:16,345
I love you.

703
01:15:25,795 --> 01:15:26,795
I love you.

704
01:15:35,965 --> 01:15:39,505
(Thank you for watching
and supporting "Doctor Shin.")

705
01:15:44,445 --> 01:15:47,285
(Doctor Shin)

706
01:17:01,725 --> 01:17:03,725
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
